209/*
210==================
211CL_ParseStartSoundPacket
212==================
213*/
214static void CL_ParseStartSoundPacket(int largesoundindex)
215{
216 vec3_t pos;
217 int channel, ent;
218 int sound_num;
219 int nvolume;
220 int field_mask;
221 float attenuation;
222 float speed;
223 int fflags = CHANNELFLAG_NONE;
224
225 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD)
226 {
227 channel = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
228
229 if (channel & (1<<15))
230 nvolume = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
231 else
232 nvolume = DEFAULT_SOUND_PACKET_VOLUME;
233
234 if (channel & (1<<14))
235 attenuation = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) / 64.0;
236 else
237 attenuation = DEFAULT_SOUND_PACKET_ATTENUATION;
238
239 speed = 1.0f;
240
241 ent = (channel>>3)&1023;
242 channel &= 7;
243
244 sound_num = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
245 }
246 else
247 {
248 field_mask = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
249
250 if (field_mask & SND_VOLUME)
251 nvolume = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
252 else
253 nvolume = DEFAULT_SOUND_PACKET_VOLUME;
254
255 if (field_mask & SND_ATTENUATION)
256 attenuation = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) / 64.0;
257 else
258 attenuation = DEFAULT_SOUND_PACKET_ATTENUATION;
259
260 if (field_mask & SND_SPEEDUSHORT4000)
261 speed = ((unsigned short)MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message)) / 4000.0f;
262 else
263 speed = 1.0f;
264
265 if (field_mask & SND_LARGEENTITY)
266 {
267 ent = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
268 channel = MSG_ReadChar(&cl_message);
269 }
270 else
271 {
272 channel = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
273 ent = channel >> 3;
274 channel &= 7;
275 }
276
277 if (largesoundindex || (field_mask & SND_LARGESOUND) || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
278 sound_num = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
279 else
280 sound_num = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
281 }
282
283 MSG_ReadVector(&cl_message, pos, cls.protocol);
284
285 if (sound_num < 0 || sound_num >= MAX_SOUNDS)
286 {
287 Con_Printf("CL_ParseStartSoundPacket: sound_num (%i) >= MAX_SOUNDS (%i)\n", sound_num, MAX_SOUNDS);
288 return;
289 }
290
291 if (ent >= MAX_EDICTS)
292 {
293 Con_Printf("CL_ParseStartSoundPacket: ent = %i", ent);
294 return;
295 }
296
297 if (ent >= cl.max_entities)
298 CL_ExpandEntities(ent);
299
300 if( !CL_VM_Event_Sound(sound_num, nvolume / 255.0f, channel, attenuation, ent, pos, fflags, speed) )
301 S_StartSound_StartPosition_Flags (ent, channel, cl.sound_precache[sound_num], pos, nvolume/255.0f, attenuation, 0, fflags, speed);
302}

304/*
305==================
306CL_KeepaliveMessage
307
308When the client is taking a long time to load stuff, send keepalive messages
309so the server doesn't disconnect.
310==================
311*/
312
313static unsigned char olddata[NET_MAXMESSAGE];
314void CL_KeepaliveMessage (qbool readmessages)
315{
316 static double lastdirtytime = 0;
317 static qbool recursive = false;
318 double dirtytime;
319 double deltatime;
320 static double countdownmsg = 0;
321 static double countdownupdate = 0;
322 sizebuf_t old;
323
324 qbool thisrecursive;
325
326 thisrecursive = recursive;
327 recursive = true;
328
329 dirtytime = Sys_DirtyTime();
330 deltatime = dirtytime - lastdirtytime;
331 lastdirtytime = dirtytime;
332 if (deltatime <= 0 || deltatime >= 1800.0)
333 return;
334
335 countdownmsg -= deltatime;
336 countdownupdate -= deltatime;
337
338 if(!thisrecursive)
339 {
340 if(cls.state != ca_dedicated)
341 {
342 if(countdownupdate <= 0) // check if time stepped backwards
343 countdownupdate = 2;
344 }
345 }
346
347 // no need if server is local and definitely not if this is a demo
348 if (sv.active || !cls.netcon || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD || cls.signon >= SIGNONS)
349 {
350 recursive = thisrecursive;
351 return;
352 }
353
354 if (readmessages)
355 {
356 // read messages from server, should just be nops
357 old = cl_message;
358 memcpy(olddata, cl_message.data, cl_message.cursize);
359
360 NetConn_ClientFrame();
361
362 cl_message = old;
363 memcpy(cl_message.data, olddata, cl_message.cursize);
364 }
365
366 if (cls.netcon && countdownmsg <= 0) // check if time stepped backwards
367 {
368 sizebuf_t msg;
369 unsigned char buf[4];
370 countdownmsg = 5;
371 // write out a nop
372 // LadyHavoc: must use unreliable because reliable could kill the sigon message!
373 Con_Print("--> client to server keepalive\n");
374 memset(&msg, 0, sizeof(msg));
375 msg.data = buf;
376 msg.maxsize = sizeof(buf);
377 MSG_WriteChar(&msg, clc_nop);
378 NetConn_SendUnreliableMessage(cls.netcon, &msg, cls.protocol, 10000, 0, false);
379 }
380
381 recursive = thisrecursive;
382}

384void CL_ParseEntityLump(char *entdata)
385{
386 qbool loadedsky = false;
387 const char *data;
388 char key[128], value[MAX_INPUTLINE];
389 FOG_clear(); // LadyHavoc: no fog until set
390 // LadyHavoc: default to the map's sky (q3 shader parsing sets this)
391 R_SetSkyBox(cl.worldmodel->brush.skybox);
392 data = entdata;
393 if (!data)
394 return;
395 if (!COM_ParseToken_Simple(&data, false, false, true))
396 return; // error
397 if (com_token[0] != '{')
398 return; // error
399 while (1)
400 {
401 if (!COM_ParseToken_Simple(&data, false, false, true))
402 return; // error
403 if (com_token[0] == '}')
404 break; // end of worldspawn
405 if (com_token[0] == '_')
406 dp_strlcpy (key, com_token + 1, sizeof (key));
407 else
408 dp_strlcpy (key, com_token, sizeof (key));
409 while (key[strlen(key)-1] == ' ') // remove trailing spaces
410 key[strlen(key)-1] = 0;
411 if (!COM_ParseToken_Simple(&data, false, false, true))
412 return; // error
413 dp_strlcpy (value, com_token, sizeof (value));
414 if (!strcmp("sky", key))
415 {
416 loadedsky = true;
417 R_SetSkyBox(value);
418 }
419 else if (!strcmp("skyname", key)) // non-standard, introduced by QuakeForge... sigh.
420 {
421 loadedsky = true;
422 R_SetSkyBox(value);
423 }
424 else if (!strcmp("qlsky", key)) // non-standard, introduced by QuakeLives (EEK)
425 {
426 loadedsky = true;
427 R_SetSkyBox(value);
428 }
429 else if (!strcmp("fog", key))
430 {
431 FOG_clear(); // so missing values get good defaults
432 r_refdef.fog_start = 0;
433 r_refdef.fog_alpha = 1;
434 r_refdef.fog_end = 16384;
435 r_refdef.fog_height = 1<<30;
436 r_refdef.fog_fadedepth = 128;
437#if _MSC_VER >= 1400
438#define sscanf sscanf_s
439#endif
440 sscanf(value, "%f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f", &r_refdef.fog_density, &r_refdef.fog_red, &r_refdef.fog_green, &r_refdef.fog_blue, &r_refdef.fog_alpha, &r_refdef.fog_start, &r_refdef.fog_end, &r_refdef.fog_height, &r_refdef.fog_fadedepth);
441 }
442 else if (!strcmp("fog_density", key))
443 r_refdef.fog_density = atof(value);
444 else if (!strcmp("fog_red", key))
445 r_refdef.fog_red = atof(value);
446 else if (!strcmp("fog_green", key))
447 r_refdef.fog_green = atof(value);
448 else if (!strcmp("fog_blue", key))
449 r_refdef.fog_blue = atof(value);
450 else if (!strcmp("fog_alpha", key))
451 r_refdef.fog_alpha = atof(value);
452 else if (!strcmp("fog_start", key))
453 r_refdef.fog_start = atof(value);
454 else if (!strcmp("fog_end", key))
455 r_refdef.fog_end = atof(value);
456 else if (!strcmp("fog_height", key))
457 r_refdef.fog_height = atof(value);
458 else if (!strcmp("fog_fadedepth", key))
459 r_refdef.fog_fadedepth = atof(value);
460 else if (!strcmp("fog_heighttexture", key))
461 {
462 FOG_clear(); // so missing values get good defaults
463#if _MSC_VER >= 1400
464 sscanf_s(value, "%f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f %s", &r_refdef.fog_density, &r_refdef.fog_red, &r_refdef.fog_green, &r_refdef.fog_blue, &r_refdef.fog_alpha, &r_refdef.fog_start, &r_refdef.fog_end, &r_refdef.fog_height, &r_refdef.fog_fadedepth, r_refdef.fog_height_texturename, (unsigned int)sizeof(r_refdef.fog_height_texturename));
465#else
466 sscanf(value, "%f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f %f %63s", &r_refdef.fog_density, &r_refdef.fog_red, &r_refdef.fog_green, &r_refdef.fog_blue, &r_refdef.fog_alpha, &r_refdef.fog_start, &r_refdef.fog_end, &r_refdef.fog_height, &r_refdef.fog_fadedepth, r_refdef.fog_height_texturename);
467#endif
468 r_refdef.fog_height_texturename[63] = 0;
469 }
470 }
471
472 if (!loadedsky && cl.worldmodel->brush.isq2bsp)
473 R_SetSkyBox("unit1_");
474}

476extern cvar_t con_chatsound_team_file;
477static const vec3_t defaultmins = {-4096, -4096, -4096};
478static const vec3_t defaultmaxs = {4096, 4096, 4096};
479static void CL_SetupWorldModel(void)
480{
481 prvm_prog_t *prog = CLVM_prog;
482 // update the world model
483 cl.entities[0].render.model = cl.worldmodel = CL_GetModelByIndex(1);
484 CL_UpdateRenderEntity(&cl.entities[0].render);
485
486 // make sure the cl.worldname and related cvars are set up now that we know the world model name
487 // set up csqc world for collision culling
488 if (cl.worldmodel)
489 {
490 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldname, cl.worldmodel->name, sizeof(cl.worldname));
491 FS_StripExtension(cl.worldname, cl.worldnamenoextension, sizeof(cl.worldnamenoextension));
492 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldbasename, !strncmp(cl.worldnamenoextension, "maps/", 5) ? cl.worldnamenoextension + 5 : cl.worldnamenoextension, sizeof(cl.worldbasename));
493 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldmessage, cl.worldmessage);
494 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldname, cl.worldname);
495 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldnamenoextension, cl.worldnamenoextension);
496 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldbasename, cl.worldbasename);
497 World_SetSize(&cl.world, cl.worldname, cl.worldmodel->normalmins, cl.worldmodel->normalmaxs, prog);
498 }
499 else
500 {
501 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldmessage, cl.worldmessage);
502 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldnamenoextension, "");
503 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldbasename, "");
504 World_SetSize(&cl.world, "", defaultmins, defaultmaxs, prog);
505 }
506 World_Start(&cl.world);
507
508 // load or reload .loc file for team chat messages
509 CL_Locs_Reload_f(cmd_local);
510
511 // make sure we send enough keepalives
512 CL_KeepaliveMessage(false);
513
514 // reset particles and other per-level things
515 R_Modules_NewMap();
516
517 // make sure we send enough keepalives
518 CL_KeepaliveMessage(false);
519
520 // load the team chat beep if possible
521 cl.foundteamchatsound = FS_FileExists(con_chatsound_team_file.string);
522
523 // check memory integrity
524 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
525
526#ifdef CONFIG_MENU
527 // make menu know
528 MR_NewMap();
529#endif
530
531 // load the csqc now
532 if (cl.loadcsqc)
533 {
534 cl.loadcsqc = false;
535
536 CL_VM_Init();
537 }

540static qbool QW_CL_CheckOrDownloadFile(const char *filename)
541{
542 qfile_t *file;
543 char vabuf[1024];
544
545 // see if the file already exists
546 file = FS_OpenVirtualFile(filename, true);
547 if (file)
548 {
549 FS_Close(file);
550 return true;
551 }
552
553 // download messages in a demo would be bad
554 if (cls.demorecording)
555 {
556 Con_Printf("Unable to download \"%s\" when recording.\n", filename);
557 return true;
558 }
559
560 // don't try to download when playing a demo
561 if (!cls.netcon)
562 return true;
563
564 dp_strlcpy(cls.qw_downloadname, filename, sizeof(cls.qw_downloadname));
565 Con_Printf("Downloading %s\n", filename);
566
567 if (!cls.qw_downloadmemory)
568 {
569 cls.qw_downloadmemory = NULL;
570 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = 0;
571 cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize = 1024*1024; // start out with a 1MB buffer
572 }
573
574 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
575 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "download %s", filename));
576
577 cls.qw_downloadnumber++;
578 cls.qw_downloadpercent = 0;
579 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = 0;
580
581 return false;
582}

584static void QW_CL_ProcessUserInfo(int slot);
585static void QW_CL_RequestNextDownload(void)
586{
587 int i;
588 char vabuf[1024];
589
590 // clear name of file that just finished
591 cls.qw_downloadname[0] = 0;
592
593 // skip the download fragment if playing a demo
594 if (!cls.netcon)
595 {
596 return;
597 }
598
599 switch (cls.qw_downloadtype)
600 {
601 case dl_single:
602 break;
603 case dl_skin:
604 if (cls.qw_downloadnumber == 0)
605 Con_Printf("Checking skins...\n");
606 for (;cls.qw_downloadnumber < cl.maxclients;cls.qw_downloadnumber++)
607 {
608 if (!cl.scores[cls.qw_downloadnumber].name[0])
609 continue;
610 // check if we need to download the file, and return if so
611 if (!QW_CL_CheckOrDownloadFile(va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "skins/%s.pcx", cl.scores[cls.qw_downloadnumber].qw_skin)))
612 return;
613 }
614
615 cls.qw_downloadtype = dl_none;
616
617 // load any newly downloaded skins
618 for (i = 0;i < cl.maxclients;i++)
619 QW_CL_ProcessUserInfo(i);
620
621 // if we're still in signon stages, request the next one
622 if (cls.signon != SIGNONS)
623 {
624 CL_SetSignonStage_WithMsg(SIGNONS - 1);
625 // we'll go to SIGNONS when the first entity update is received
626 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
627 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "begin %i", cl.qw_servercount));
628 }
629 break;
630 case dl_model:
631 if (cls.qw_downloadnumber == 0)
632 {
633 Con_Printf("Checking models...\n");
634 cls.qw_downloadnumber = 1;
635 }
636
637 for (;cls.qw_downloadnumber < MAX_MODELS && cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber][0];cls.qw_downloadnumber++)
638 {
639 // skip submodels
640 if (cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber][0] == '*')
641 continue;
642 if (!strcmp(cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber], "progs/spike.mdl"))
643 cl.qw_modelindex_spike = cls.qw_downloadnumber;
644 if (!strcmp(cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber], "progs/player.mdl"))
645 cl.qw_modelindex_player = cls.qw_downloadnumber;
646 if (!strcmp(cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber], "progs/flag.mdl"))
647 cl.qw_modelindex_flag = cls.qw_downloadnumber;
648 if (!strcmp(cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber], "progs/s_explod.spr"))
649 cl.qw_modelindex_s_explod = cls.qw_downloadnumber;
650 // check if we need to download the file, and return if so
651 if (!QW_CL_CheckOrDownloadFile(cl.model_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber]))
652 return;
653 }
654
655 cls.qw_downloadtype = dl_none;
656
657 // touch all of the precached models that are still loaded so we can free
658 // anything that isn't needed
659 if (!sv.active)
660 Mod_ClearUsed();
661 for (i = 1;i < MAX_MODELS && cl.model_name[i][0];i++)
662 Mod_FindName(cl.model_name[i], cl.model_name[i][0] == '*' ? cl.model_name[1] : NULL);
663 // precache any models used by the client (this also marks them used)
664 cl.model_bolt = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt.mdl", false, false, NULL);
665 cl.model_bolt2 = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt2.mdl", false, false, NULL);
666 cl.model_bolt3 = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt3.mdl", false, false, NULL);
667 cl.model_beam = Mod_ForName("progs/beam.mdl", false, false, NULL);
668
669 // we purge the models and sounds later in CL_SignonReply
670 //Mod_PurgeUnused();
671
672 // now we try to load everything that is new
673
674 // world model
675 cl.model_precache[1] = Mod_ForName(cl.model_name[1], false, false, NULL);
676 if (cl.model_precache[1]->Draw == NULL)
677 Con_Printf("Map %s could not be found or downloaded\n", cl.model_name[1]);
678
679 // normal models
680 for (i = 2;i < MAX_MODELS && cl.model_name[i][0];i++)
681 if ((cl.model_precache[i] = Mod_ForName(cl.model_name[i], false, false, cl.model_name[i][0] == '*' ? cl.model_name[1] : NULL))->Draw == NULL)
682 Con_Printf("Model %s could not be found or downloaded\n", cl.model_name[i]);
683
684 // check memory integrity
685 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
686
687 // now that we have a world model, set up the world entity, renderer
688 // modules and csqc
689 CL_SetupWorldModel();
690
691 // add pmodel/emodel CRCs to userinfo
692 CL_SetInfo("pmodel", va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "%i", FS_CRCFile("progs/player.mdl", NULL)), true, true, true, true);
693 CL_SetInfo("emodel", va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "%i", FS_CRCFile("progs/eyes.mdl", NULL)), true, true, true, true);
694
695 // done checking sounds and models, send a prespawn command now
696 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
697 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "prespawn %i 0 %i", cl.qw_servercount, cl.model_precache[1]->brush.qw_md4sum2));
698
699 if (cls.qw_downloadmemory)
700 {
701 Mem_Free(cls.qw_downloadmemory);
702 cls.qw_downloadmemory = NULL;
703 }
704
705 // done loading
706 cl.loadfinished = true;
707 break;
708 case dl_sound:
709 if (cls.qw_downloadnumber == 0)
710 {
711 Con_Printf("Checking sounds...\n");
712 cls.qw_downloadnumber = 1;
713 }
714
715 for (;cl.sound_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber][0];cls.qw_downloadnumber++)
716 {
717 // check if we need to download the file, and return if so
718 if (!QW_CL_CheckOrDownloadFile(va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "sound/%s", cl.sound_name[cls.qw_downloadnumber])))
719 return;
720 }
721
722 cls.qw_downloadtype = dl_none;
723
724 // clear sound usage flags for purging of unused sounds
725 S_ClearUsed();
726
727 // precache any sounds used by the client
728 cl.sfx_wizhit = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_wizardhit.string, false, true);
729 cl.sfx_knighthit = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_hknighthit.string, false, true);
730 cl.sfx_tink1 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_tink1.string, false, true);
731 cl.sfx_ric1 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric1.string, false, true);
732 cl.sfx_ric2 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric2.string, false, true);
733 cl.sfx_ric3 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric3.string, false, true);
734 cl.sfx_r_exp3 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_r_exp3.string, false, true);
735
736 // sounds used by the game
737 for (i = 1;i < MAX_SOUNDS && cl.sound_name[i][0];i++)
738 cl.sound_precache[i] = S_PrecacheSound(cl.sound_name[i], true, true);
739
740 // we purge the models and sounds later in CL_SignonReply
741 //S_PurgeUnused();
742
743 // check memory integrity
744 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
745
746 // done with sound downloads, next we check models
747 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
748 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "modellist %i %i", cl.qw_servercount, 0));
749 break;
750 case dl_none:
751 default:
752 Con_Printf("Unknown download type.\n");
753 }
754}

756static void QW_CL_ParseDownload(void)
757{
758 int size = (signed short)MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
759 int percent = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
760
761 //Con_Printf("download %i %i%% (%i/%i)\n", size, percent, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize, cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize);
762
763 // skip the download fragment if playing a demo
764 if (!cls.netcon)
765 {
766 if (size > 0)
767 cl_message.readcount += size;
768 return;
769 }
770
771 if (size == -1)
772 {
773 Con_Printf("File not found.\n");
774 QW_CL_RequestNextDownload();
775 return;
776 }
777
778 if (cl_message.readcount + (unsigned short)size > cl_message.cursize)
779 Host_Error("corrupt download message\n");
780
781 // make sure the buffer is big enough to include this new fragment
782 if (!cls.qw_downloadmemory || cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize < cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize + size)
783 {
784 unsigned char *old;
785 while (cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize < cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize + size)
786 cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize *= 2;
787 old = cls.qw_downloadmemory;
788 cls.qw_downloadmemory = (unsigned char *)Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize);
789 if (old)
790 {
791 memcpy(cls.qw_downloadmemory, old, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
792 Mem_Free(old);
793 }
794 }
795
796 // read the fragment out of the packet
797 MSG_ReadBytes(&cl_message, size, cls.qw_downloadmemory + cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
798 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize += size;
799 cls.qw_downloadspeedcount += size;
800
801 cls.qw_downloadpercent = percent;
802
803 if (percent != 100)
804 {
805 // request next fragment
806 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
807 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, "nextdl");
808 }
809 else
810 {
811 // finished file
812 Con_Printf("Downloaded \"%s\"\n", cls.qw_downloadname);
813
814 FS_WriteFile(cls.qw_downloadname, cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
815
816 cls.qw_downloadpercent = 0;
817
818 // start downloading the next file (or join the game)
819 QW_CL_RequestNextDownload();
820 }
821}

823static void QW_CL_ParseModelList(void)
824{
825 int n;
826 int nummodels = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
827 char *str;
828 char vabuf[1024];
829
830 // parse model precache list
831 for (;;)
832 {
833 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
834 if (!str[0])
835 break;
836 nummodels++;
837 if (nummodels==MAX_MODELS)
838 Host_Error("Server sent too many model precaches");
839 if (strlen(str) >= MAX_QPATH)
840 Host_Error("Server sent a precache name of %i characters (max %i)", (int)strlen(str), MAX_QPATH - 1);
841 dp_strlcpy(cl.model_name[nummodels], str, sizeof (cl.model_name[nummodels]));
842 }
843
844 n = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
845 if (n)
846 {
847 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
848 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "modellist %i %i", cl.qw_servercount, n));
849 return;
850 }
851
852 CL_SetSignonStage_WithMsg(2);
853 cls.qw_downloadnumber = 0;
854 cls.qw_downloadtype = dl_model;
855 QW_CL_RequestNextDownload();
856}

912void QW_CL_NextUpload_f(cmd_state_t *cmd)
913{
914 int r, percent, size;
915
916 if (!cls.qw_uploaddata)
917 return;
918
919 r = cls.qw_uploadsize - cls.qw_uploadpos;
920 if (r > 768)
921 r = 768;
922 size = min(1, cls.qw_uploadsize);
923 percent = (cls.qw_uploadpos+r)*100/size;
924
925 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_upload);
926 MSG_WriteShort(&cls.netcon->message, r);
927 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, percent);
928 SZ_Write(&cls.netcon->message, cls.qw_uploaddata + cls.qw_uploadpos, r);
929
930 Con_DPrintf("UPLOAD: %6d: %d written\n", cls.qw_uploadpos, r);
931
932 cls.qw_uploadpos += r;
933
934 if (cls.qw_uploadpos < cls.qw_uploadsize)
935 return;
936
937 Con_Printf("Upload completed\n");
938
939 QW_CL_StopUpload_f(cmd);
940}

942void QW_CL_StartUpload(unsigned char *data, int size)
943{
944 // do nothing in demos or if not connected
945 if (!cls.netcon)
946 return;
947
948 // abort existing upload if in progress
949 QW_CL_StopUpload_f(cmd_local);
950
951 Con_DPrintf("Starting upload of %d bytes...\n", size);
952
953 cls.qw_uploaddata = (unsigned char *)Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, size);
954 memcpy(cls.qw_uploaddata, data, size);
955 cls.qw_uploadsize = size;
956 cls.qw_uploadpos = 0;
957
958 QW_CL_NextUpload_f(cmd_local);
959}

1042static void QW_CL_ParseNails(void)
1043{
1044 int i, j;
1045 int numnails = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
1046 vec_t *v;
1047 unsigned char bits[6];
1048 for (i = 0;i < numnails;i++)
1049 {
1050 for (j = 0;j < 6;j++)
1051 bits[j] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
1052 if (cl.qw_num_nails >= 255)
1053 continue;
1054 v = cl.qw_nails[cl.qw_num_nails++];
1055 v[0] = ( ( bits[0] + ((bits[1]&15)<<8) ) <<1) - 4096;
1056 v[1] = ( ( (bits[1]>>4) + (bits[2]<<4) ) <<1) - 4096;
1057 v[2] = ( ( bits[3] + ((bits[4]&15)<<8) ) <<1) - 4096;
1058 v[3] = -360*(bits[4]>>4)/16;
1059 v[4] = 360*bits[5]/256;
1060 v[5] = 0;
1061 }
1062}

1064static void CL_UpdateItemsAndWeapon(void)
1065{
1066 int j;
1067 // check for important changes
1068
1069 // set flash times
1070 // UBSan: unsigned literals because left shifting by 31 causes signed overflow, although it works as expected on x86.
1071 if (cl.olditems != cl.stats[STAT_ITEMS])
1072 for (j = 0;j < 32;j++)
1073 if ((cl.stats[STAT_ITEMS] & (1u<<j)) && !(cl.olditems & (1u<<j)))
1074 cl.item_gettime[j] = cl.time;
1075 cl.olditems = cl.stats[STAT_ITEMS];
1076
1077 // GAME_NEXUIZ hud needs weapon change time
1078 if (cl.activeweapon != cl.stats[STAT_ACTIVEWEAPON])
1079 cl.weapontime = cl.time;
1080 cl.activeweapon = cl.stats[STAT_ACTIVEWEAPON];
1081}

1088static void CL_BeginDownloads(qbool aborteddownload)
1089{
1090 char vabuf[1024];
1091 // quakeworld works differently
1092 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD)
1093 return;
1094
1095 // this would be a good place to do curl downloads
1096 if(Curl_Have_forthismap())
1097 {
1098 Curl_Register_predownload(); // come back later
1099 return;
1100 }
1101
1102 // if we got here...
1103 // curl is done, so let's start with the business
1104 if(!cl.loadbegun)
1105 SCR_PushLoadingScreen("Loading precaches", 1);
1106 cl.loadbegun = true;
1107
1108 // if already downloading something from the previous level, don't stop it
1109 if (cls.qw_downloadname[0])
1110 return;
1111
1112 if (cl.downloadcsqc)
1113 {
1114 size_t progsize;
1115 cl.downloadcsqc = false;
1116 if (cls.netcon
1117 && !sv.active
1118 && csqc_progname.string
1119 && csqc_progname.string[0]
1120 && csqc_progcrc.integer >= 0
1121 && cl_serverextension_download.integer
1122 && (FS_CRCFile(csqc_progname.string, &progsize) != csqc_progcrc.integer || ((int)progsize != csqc_progsize.integer && csqc_progsize.integer != -1))
1123 && !FS_FileExists(va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "dlcache/%s.%i.%i", csqc_progname.string, csqc_progsize.integer, csqc_progcrc.integer)))
1124 {

1126 if(cl_serverextension_download.integer == 2 && FS_HasZlib())
1127 CL_ForwardToServer(va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "download %s deflate", csqc_progname.string));
1128 else
1129 CL_ForwardToServer(va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "download %s", csqc_progname.string));
1130 return;
1131 }
1132 }
1133
1134 if (cl.loadmodel_current < cl.loadmodel_total)
1135 {
1136 // loading models
1137 if(cl.loadmodel_current == 1)
1138 {

1144 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL_INIT
1145 ) / (
1146 (cl.loadmodel_total - 1) * LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_MODEL
1147 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL
1148 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL_INIT
1149 + cl.loadsound_total * LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_SOUND

1151 );

1156 (

1159 (cl.loadmodel_total - 1) * LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_MODEL
1160 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL
1161 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL_INIT
1162 )

1170 SCR_PopLoadingScreen(false);
1171 }

1177 if (sv.active)
1178 cl.model_precache[cl.loadmodel_current] = sv.models[cl.loadmodel_current];
1179 else

1181 if(cl.loadmodel_current == 1)
1182 {

1184 Mod_FreeQ3Shaders();
1185 }

1187 }
1188 SCR_PopLoadingScreen(false);
1189 if (cl.model_precache[cl.loadmodel_current] && cl.model_precache[cl.loadmodel_current]->Draw && cl.loadmodel_current == 1)
1190 {

1195 ) / (

1198 + LOADPROGRESSWEIGHT_WORLDMODEL_INIT
1199 )

1250 // until this is fixed, only support pk3 downloads via curl, and turn off
1251 // individual file downloads other than for CSQC
1252 // on the other end of the download protocol, GAME_NEXUIZ/GAME_XONOTIC enforces writing
1253 // to dlcache only
1254 // idea: support download of pk3 files using this protocol later
1255

1272 CL_SetupWorldModel();

1279 }
1280 }

1299 }
1300 }
1301
1302 if(cl.downloadmodel_current == 1)
1303 {

1305 Mod_FreeQ3Shaders();
1306 }

1309 if (cl.downloadmodel_current == 1)
1310 {
1311 // we now have the worldmodel so we can set up the game world
1312 // or maybe we do not have it (cl_serverextension_download 0)

1314 CL_SetupWorldModel();
1315 if (!cl.loadfinished && cl_joinbeforedownloadsfinish.integer)
1316 {
1317 cl.loadfinished = true;

1320 CL_ForwardToServer("prespawn");
1321 }
1322 }
1323 }
1324
1325 // finished loading models
1326 }

1384static void CL_StopDownload(int size, int crc)
1385{
1386 if (cls.qw_downloadmemory && cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize == size && CRC_Block(cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize) == crc)
1387 {
1388 int existingcrc;
1389 size_t existingsize;
1390 const char *extension;
1391
1392 if(cls.qw_download_deflate)
1393 {
1394 unsigned char *out;
1395 size_t inflated_size;
1396 out = FS_Inflate(cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize, &inflated_size, tempmempool);
1397 Mem_Free(cls.qw_downloadmemory);
1398 if(out)
1399 {
1400 Con_Printf("Inflated download: new size: %u (%g%%)\n", (unsigned)inflated_size, 100.0 - 100.0*(cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize / (float)inflated_size));
1401 cls.qw_downloadmemory = out;
1402 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = (int)inflated_size;
1403 }
1404 else
1405 {
1406 cls.qw_downloadmemory = NULL;
1407 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = 0;
1408 Con_Printf("Cannot inflate download, possibly corrupt or zlib not present\n");
1409 }
1410 }
1411
1412 if(!cls.qw_downloadmemory)
1413 {
1414 Con_Printf("Download \"%s\" is corrupt (see above!)\n", cls.qw_downloadname);
1415 }
1416 else
1417 {
1418 crc = CRC_Block(cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
1419 size = cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize;
1420 // finished file
1421 // save to disk only if we don't already have it
1422 // (this is mainly for playing back demos)
1423 existingcrc = FS_CRCFile(cls.qw_downloadname, &existingsize);
1424 if (existingsize || IS_NEXUIZ_DERIVED(gamemode) || !strcmp(cls.qw_downloadname, csqc_progname.string))
1425 // let csprogs ALWAYS go to dlcache, to prevent "viral csprogs"; also, never put files outside dlcache for Nexuiz/Xonotic
1426 {
1427 if ((int)existingsize != size || existingcrc != crc)
1428 {
1429 // we have a mismatching file, pick another name for it
1430 char name[MAX_QPATH*2];
1431 dpsnprintf(name, sizeof(name), "dlcache/%s.%i.%i", cls.qw_downloadname, size, crc);
1432 if (!FS_FileExists(name))
1433 {
1434 Con_Printf("Downloaded \"%s\" (%i bytes, %i CRC)\n", name, size, crc);
1435 FS_WriteFile(name, cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
1436 if(!strcmp(cls.qw_downloadname, csqc_progname.string))
1437 {
1438 if(cls.caughtcsprogsdata)
1439 Mem_Free(cls.caughtcsprogsdata);
1440 cls.caughtcsprogsdata = (unsigned char *) Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
1441 memcpy(cls.caughtcsprogsdata, cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
1442 cls.caughtcsprogsdatasize = cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize;
1443 Con_DPrintf("Buffered \"%s\"\n", name);
1444 }
1445 }
1446 }
1447 }
1448 else
1449 {
1450 // we either don't have it or have a mismatching file...
1451 // so it's time to accept the file
1452 // but if we already have a mismatching file we need to rename
1453 // this new one, and if we already have this file in renamed form,
1454 // we do nothing
1455 Con_Printf("Downloaded \"%s\" (%i bytes, %i CRC)\n", cls.qw_downloadname, size, crc);
1456 FS_WriteFile(cls.qw_downloadname, cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize);
1457 extension = FS_FileExtension(cls.qw_downloadname);
1458 if (!strcasecmp(extension, "pak") || !strcasecmp(extension, "pk3") || !strcasecmp(extension, "dpk"))
1459 FS_Rescan();
1460 }
1461 }
1462 }
1463 else if (cls.qw_downloadmemory && size)
1464 {
1465 Con_Printf("Download \"%s\" is corrupt (%i bytes, %i CRC, should be %i bytes, %i CRC), discarding\n", cls.qw_downloadname, size, crc, (int)cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize, (int)CRC_Block(cls.qw_downloadmemory, cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize));
1466 CL_BeginDownloads(true);
1467 }
1468
1469 if (cls.qw_downloadmemory)
1470 Mem_Free(cls.qw_downloadmemory);
1471 cls.qw_downloadmemory = NULL;
1472 cls.qw_downloadname[0] = 0;
1473 cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize = 0;
1474 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = 0;
1475 cls.qw_downloadpercent = 0;
1476}
1477
1478static void CL_ParseDownload(void)
1479{
1480 int i, start, size;
1481 static unsigned char data[NET_MAXMESSAGE];
1482 start = MSG_ReadLong(&cl_message);
1483 size = (unsigned short)MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
1484
1485 // record the start/size information to ack in the next input packet
1486 for (i = 0;i < CL_MAX_DOWNLOADACKS;i++)
1487 {
1488 if (!cls.dp_downloadack[i].start && !cls.dp_downloadack[i].size)
1489 {
1490 cls.dp_downloadack[i].start = start;
1491 cls.dp_downloadack[i].size = size;
1492 break;
1493 }
1494 }
1495
1496 MSG_ReadBytes(&cl_message, size, data);
1497
1498 if (!cls.qw_downloadname[0])
1499 {
1500 if (size > 0)
1501 Con_Printf("CL_ParseDownload: received %i bytes with no download active\n", size);
1502 return;
1503 }
1504
1505 if (start + size > cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize)
1506 Host_Error("corrupt download message\n");
1507
1508 // only advance cursize if the data is at the expected position
1509 // (gaps are unacceptable)
1510 memcpy(cls.qw_downloadmemory + start, data, size);
1511 cls.qw_downloadmemorycursize = start + size;
1512 cls.qw_downloadpercent = (int)floor((start+size) * 100.0 / cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize);
1513 cls.qw_downloadpercent = bound(0, cls.qw_downloadpercent, 100);
1514 cls.qw_downloadspeedcount += size;
1515}

1517static void CL_DownloadBegin_f(cmd_state_t *cmd)
1518{
1519 int size = atoi(Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1));
1520
1521 if (size < 0 || size > 1<<30 || FS_CheckNastyPath(Cmd_Argv(cmd, 2), false))
1522 {
1523 Con_Printf("cl_downloadbegin: received bogus information\n");
1524 CL_StopDownload(0, 0);
1525 return;
1526 }
1527
1528 if (cls.qw_downloadname[0])
1529 Con_Printf("Download of %s aborted\n", cls.qw_downloadname);
1530
1531 CL_StopDownload(0, 0);
1532
1533 // we're really beginning a download now, so initialize stuff
1534 dp_strlcpy(cls.qw_downloadname, Cmd_Argv(cmd, 2), sizeof(cls.qw_downloadname));
1535 cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize = size;
1536 cls.qw_downloadmemory = (unsigned char *) Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, cls.qw_downloadmemorymaxsize);
1537 cls.qw_downloadnumber++;
1538
1539 cls.qw_download_deflate = false;
1540 if(Cmd_Argc(cmd) >= 4)
1541 {
1542 if(!strcmp(Cmd_Argv(cmd, 3), "deflate"))
1543 cls.qw_download_deflate = true;
1544 // check further encodings here
1545 }
1546
1547 CL_ForwardToServer("sv_startdownload");
1548}

1606/*
1607=====================
1608CL_SignonReply
1609
1610An svc_signonnum has been received, perform a client side setup
1611=====================
1612*/
1613static void CL_SignonReply(int signon_stage)
1614{
1615 CL_SetSignonStage_WithMsg(signon_stage);
1616
1617 Con_DPrintf("CL_SignonReply: %i\n", cls.signon);
1618
1619 switch (cls.signon)
1620 {
1621 case 1:
1622 if (cls.netcon)
1623 {
1624 // send player info before we begin downloads
1625 // (so that the server can see the player name while downloading)
1626 CL_SendPlayerInfo();
1627
1628 //MSG_WriteByte (&cls.netcon->message, clc_stringcmd);
1629 //MSG_WriteString (&cls.netcon->message, "prespawn");
1630 }
1631 // execute cl_begindownloads next frame
1632 // (after any commands added by svc_stufftext have been executed)
1633 // when done with downloads the "prespawn" will be sent
1634 Cbuf_AddText(cmd_local, "\ncl_begindownloads\n");
1635 break;
1636
1637 case 2:
1638 if (cls.netcon)
1639 {
1640 // LadyHavoc: quake sent the player info here but due to downloads
1641 // it is sent earlier instead
1642 // CL_SendPlayerInfo();
1643
1644 // LadyHavoc: changed to begin a loading stage and issue this when done
1645 MSG_WriteByte (&cls.netcon->message, clc_stringcmd);
1646 MSG_WriteString (&cls.netcon->message, "spawn");
1647 }
1648 break;
1649
1650 case 3:
1651 if (cls.netcon)
1652 {
1653 MSG_WriteByte (&cls.netcon->message, clc_stringcmd);
1654 MSG_WriteString (&cls.netcon->message, "begin");
1655 }
1656 break;
1657
1658 case 4:
1659 // after the level has been loaded, we shouldn't need the shaders, and
1660 // if they are needed again they will be automatically loaded...
1661 // we also don't need the unused models or sounds from the last level
1662 Mod_FreeQ3Shaders();
1663 Mod_PurgeUnused();
1664 S_PurgeUnused();
1665
1666 Con_ClearNotify();
1667 if (Sys_CheckParm("-profilegameonly"))
1668 Sys_AllowProfiling(true);
1669 break;
1670 }
1671}

1673/*
1674==================
1675CL_ParseServerInfo
1676==================
1677*/
1678static void CL_ParseServerInfo (void)
1679{
1680 char *str;
1681 int i;
1682 protocolversion_t protocol;
1683 int nummodels, numsounds;
1684 char vabuf[1024];
1685
1686 // if we start loading a level and a video is still playing, stop it
1687 CL_VideoStop();
1688
1689 Con_DPrint("Serverinfo packet received.\n");
1690 Collision_Cache_Reset(true);
1691
1692 // if server is active, we already began a loading plaque
1693 if (!sv.active)
1694 {
1695 SCR_BeginLoadingPlaque(false);
1696 S_StopAllSounds();
1697 // prevent dlcache assets from the previous map from interfering with this one
1698 FS_UnloadPacks_dlcache();
1699 // free q3 shaders so that any newly downloaded shaders will be active
1700 // bones_was_here: we free the q3 shaders later in CL_SignonReply
1701 //Mod_FreeQ3Shaders();
1702 }
1703
1704 // check memory integrity
1705 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
1706
1707 // clear cl_serverextension cvars
1708 Cvar_SetValueQuick(&cl_serverextension_download, 0);
1709
1710//
1711// wipe the client_state_t struct
1712//
1713 CL_ClearState ();
1714
1715// parse protocol version number
1716 i = MSG_ReadLong(&cl_message);
1717 protocol = Protocol_EnumForNumber(i);
1718 if (protocol == PROTOCOL_UNKNOWN)
1719 {
1720 Host_Error("CL_ParseServerInfo: Server is unrecognized protocol number (%i)", i);
1721 return;
1722 }
1723 // hack for unmarked Nehahra movie demos which had a custom protocol
1724 if (protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP && cls.demoplayback && gamemode == GAME_NEHAHRA)
1725 protocol = PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE;
1726 cls.protocol = protocol;
1727 Con_Printf("Server protocol is %s\n", Protocol_NameForEnum(cls.protocol));
1728
1729 cl.num_entities = 1;
1730
1731 if (protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD)
1732 {
1733 char gamedir[1][MAX_QPATH];
1734
1735 cl.qw_servercount = MSG_ReadLong(&cl_message);
1736
1737 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
1738 Con_Printf("server gamedir is %s\n", str);
1739 dp_strlcpy(gamedir[0], str, sizeof(gamedir[0]));
1740
1741 // change gamedir if needed
1742 if (!FS_ChangeGameDirs(1, gamedir, true, false))
1743 Host_Error("CL_ParseServerInfo: unable to switch to server specified gamedir");
1744
1745 cl.gametype = GAME_DEATHMATCH;
1746 cl.maxclients = 32;
1747
1748 // parse player number
1749 i = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
1750 // cl.qw_spectator is an unneeded flag, cl.scores[cl.playerentity].qw_spectator works better (it can be updated by the server during the game)
1751 //cl.qw_spectator = (i & 128) != 0;
1752 cl.realplayerentity = cl.playerentity = cl.viewentity = (i & 127) + 1;
1753 cl.scores = (scoreboard_t *)Mem_Alloc(cls.levelmempool, cl.maxclients*sizeof(*cl.scores));
1754
1755 // get the full level name
1756 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
1757 dp_strlcpy (cl.worldmessage, str, sizeof(cl.worldmessage));
1758
1759 // get the movevars that are defined in the qw protocol
1760 cl.movevars_gravity = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1761 cl.movevars_stopspeed = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1762 cl.movevars_maxspeed = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1763 cl.movevars_spectatormaxspeed = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1764 cl.movevars_accelerate = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1765 cl.movevars_airaccelerate = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1766 cl.movevars_wateraccelerate = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1767 cl.movevars_friction = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1768 cl.movevars_waterfriction = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1769 cl.movevars_entgravity = MSG_ReadFloat(&cl_message);
1770
1771 // other movevars not in the protocol...
1772 cl.movevars_wallfriction = 0;
1773 cl.movevars_timescale = 1;
1774 cl.movevars_jumpvelocity = 270;
1775 cl.movevars_edgefriction = 1;
1776 cl.movevars_maxairspeed = 30;
1777 cl.movevars_stepheight = 18;
1778 cl.movevars_airaccel_qw = 1;
1779 cl.movevars_airaccel_sideways_friction = 0;
1780
1781 // seperate the printfs so the server message can have a color
1782 Con_Printf("\n\n<===================================>\n\n\2%s\n", str);
1783
1784 // check memory integrity
1785 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
1786
1787 if (cls.netcon)
1788 {
1789 MSG_WriteByte(&cls.netcon->message, qw_clc_stringcmd);
1790 MSG_WriteString(&cls.netcon->message, va(vabuf, sizeof(vabuf), "soundlist %i %i", cl.qw_servercount, 0));
1791 }
1792
1793 cl.loadbegun = false;
1794 cl.loadfinished = false;
1795
1796 cls.state = ca_connected;
1797 CL_SetSignonStage_WithMsg(1);
1798
1799 // note: on QW protocol we can't set up the gameworld until after
1800 // downloads finish...
1801 // (we don't even know the name of the map yet)
1802 // this also means cl_autodemo does not work on QW protocol...
1803
1804 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldname, "", sizeof(cl.worldname));
1805 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldnamenoextension, "", sizeof(cl.worldnamenoextension));
1806 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldbasename, "qw", sizeof(cl.worldbasename));
1807 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldname, cl.worldname);
1808 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldnamenoextension, cl.worldnamenoextension);
1809 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldbasename, cl.worldbasename);
1810
1811 // check memory integrity
1812 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
1813 }
1814 else
1815 {
1816 // parse maxclients
1817 cl.maxclients = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
1818 if (cl.maxclients < 1 || cl.maxclients > MAX_SCOREBOARD)
1819 {
1820 Host_Error("Bad maxclients (%u) from server", cl.maxclients);
1821 return;
1822 }
1823 cl.scores = (scoreboard_t *)Mem_Alloc(cls.levelmempool, cl.maxclients*sizeof(*cl.scores));
1824
1825 // parse gametype
1826 cl.gametype = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
1827 // the original id singleplayer demos are bugged and contain
1828 // GAME_DEATHMATCH even for singleplayer
1829 if (cl.maxclients == 1 && cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE)
1830 cl.gametype = GAME_COOP;
1831
1832 // parse signon message
1833 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
1834 dp_strlcpy (cl.worldmessage, str, sizeof(cl.worldmessage));
1835
1836 // seperate the printfs so the server message can have a color
1837 if (cls.protocol != PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE) // no messages when playing the Nehahra movie
1838 Con_Printf("\n<===================================>\n\n\2%s\n", str);
1839
1840 // check memory integrity
1841 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
1842
1843 // parse model precache list
1844 for (nummodels=1 ; ; nummodels++)
1845 {
1846 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
1847 if (!str[0])
1848 break;
1849 if (nummodels==MAX_MODELS)
1850 Host_Error ("Server sent too many model precaches");
1851 if (strlen(str) >= MAX_QPATH)
1852 Host_Error ("Server sent a precache name of %i characters (max %i)", (int)strlen(str), MAX_QPATH - 1);
1853 dp_strlcpy (cl.model_name[nummodels], str, sizeof (cl.model_name[nummodels]));
1854 }
1855 // parse sound precache list
1856 for (numsounds=1 ; ; numsounds++)
1857 {
1858 str = MSG_ReadString(&cl_message, cl_readstring, sizeof(cl_readstring));
1859 if (!str[0])
1860 break;
1861 if (numsounds==MAX_SOUNDS)
1862 Host_Error("Server sent too many sound precaches");
1863 if (strlen(str) >= MAX_QPATH)
1864 Host_Error("Server sent a precache name of %i characters (max %i)", (int)strlen(str), MAX_QPATH - 1);
1865 dp_strlcpy (cl.sound_name[numsounds], str, sizeof (cl.sound_name[numsounds]));
1866 }
1867
1868 // set the base name for level-specific things... this gets updated again by CL_SetupWorldModel later
1869 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldname, cl.model_name[1], sizeof(cl.worldname));
1870 FS_StripExtension(cl.worldname, cl.worldnamenoextension, sizeof(cl.worldnamenoextension));
1871 dp_strlcpy(cl.worldbasename, !strncmp(cl.worldnamenoextension, "maps/", 5) ? cl.worldnamenoextension + 5 : cl.worldnamenoextension, sizeof(cl.worldbasename));
1872 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldmessage, cl.worldmessage);
1873 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldname, cl.worldname);
1874 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldnamenoextension, cl.worldnamenoextension);
1875 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_worldbasename, cl.worldbasename);
1876
1877 // touch all of the precached models that are still loaded so we can free
1878 // anything that isn't needed
1879 if (!sv.active)
1880 Mod_ClearUsed();
1881 for (i = 1;i < nummodels;i++)
1882 Mod_FindName(cl.model_name[i], cl.model_name[i][0] == '*' ? cl.model_name[1] : NULL);
1883 // precache any models used by the client (this also marks them used)
1884 cl.model_bolt = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt.mdl", false, false, NULL);
1885 cl.model_bolt2 = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt2.mdl", false, false, NULL);
1886 cl.model_bolt3 = Mod_ForName("progs/bolt3.mdl", false, false, NULL);
1887 cl.model_beam = Mod_ForName("progs/beam.mdl", false, false, NULL);
1888
1889 // we purge the models and sounds later in CL_SignonReply
1890 //Mod_PurgeUnused();
1891 //S_PurgeUnused();
1892
1893 // clear sound usage flags for purging of unused sounds
1894 S_ClearUsed();
1895
1896 // precache any sounds used by the client
1897 cl.sfx_wizhit = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_wizardhit.string, false, true);
1898 cl.sfx_knighthit = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_hknighthit.string, false, true);
1899 cl.sfx_tink1 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_tink1.string, false, true);
1900 cl.sfx_ric1 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric1.string, false, true);
1901 cl.sfx_ric2 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric2.string, false, true);
1902 cl.sfx_ric3 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_ric3.string, false, true);
1903 cl.sfx_r_exp3 = S_PrecacheSound(cl_sound_r_exp3.string, false, true);
1904
1905 // sounds used by the game
1906 for (i = 1;i < MAX_SOUNDS && cl.sound_name[i][0];i++)
1907 cl.sound_precache[i] = S_PrecacheSound(cl.sound_name[i], true, true);
1908
1909 // now we try to load everything that is new
1910 cl.loadmodel_current = 1;
1911 cl.downloadmodel_current = 1;
1912 cl.loadmodel_total = nummodels;
1913 cl.loadsound_current = 1;
1914 cl.downloadsound_current = 1;
1915 cl.loadsound_total = numsounds;
1916 cl.downloadcsqc = true;
1917 cl.loadbegun = false;
1918 cl.loadfinished = false;
1919 cl.loadcsqc = true;
1920
1921 // check memory integrity
1922 Mem_CheckSentinelsGlobal();
1923
1924 // if cl_autodemo is set, automatically start recording a demo if one isn't being recorded already
1925 if (cl_autodemo.integer && cls.netcon && cls.protocol != PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD)
1926 {
1927 char demofile[MAX_OSPATH];
1928
1929 if (cls.demorecording)
1930 {
1931 // finish the previous level's demo file
1932 CL_Stop_f(cmd_local);
1933 }
1934
1935 // start a new demo file
1936 dpsnprintf (demofile, sizeof(demofile), "%s_%s.dem", Sys_TimeString (cl_autodemo_nameformat.string), cl.worldbasename);
1937
1938 Con_Printf ("Auto-recording to %s.\n", demofile);
1939
1940 // Reset bit 0 for every new demo
1941 Cvar_SetValueQuick(&cl_autodemo_delete,
1942 (cl_autodemo_delete.integer & ~0x1)
1943 |
1944 ((cl_autodemo_delete.integer & 0x2) ? 0x1 : 0)
1945 );
1946
1947 cls.demofile = FS_OpenRealFile(demofile, "wb", false);
1948 if (cls.demofile)
1949 {
1950 cls.forcetrack = -1;
1951 FS_Printf (cls.demofile, "%i\n", cls.forcetrack);
1952 cls.demorecording = true;
1953 dp_strlcpy(cls.demoname, demofile, sizeof(cls.demoname));
1954 cls.demo_lastcsprogssize = -1;
1955 cls.demo_lastcsprogscrc = -1;
1956 }
1957 else
1958 Con_Print(CON_ERROR "ERROR: couldn't open.\n");
1959 }
1960 }
1961 cl.islocalgame = NetConn_IsLocalGame();
1962}

1964void CL_ValidateState(entity_state_t *s)
1965{
1966 model_t *model;
1967
1968 if (!s->active)
1969 return;
1970
1971 if (s->modelindex >= MAX_MODELS)
1972 Host_Error("CL_ValidateState: modelindex (%i) >= MAX_MODELS (%i)\n", s->modelindex, MAX_MODELS);
1973
1974 // these warnings are only warnings, no corrections are made to the state
1975 // because states are often copied for decoding, which otherwise would
1976 // propogate some of the corrections accidentally
1977 // (this used to happen, sometimes affecting skin and frame)
1978
1979 // colormap is client index + 1
1980 if (!(s->flags & RENDER_COLORMAPPED) && s->colormap > cl.maxclients)
1981 Con_DPrintf("CL_ValidateState: colormap (%i) > cl.maxclients (%i)\n", s->colormap, cl.maxclients);
1982
1983 if (developer_extra.integer)
1984 {
1985 model = CL_GetModelByIndex(s->modelindex);
1986 if (model && model->type && s->frame >= model->numframes)
1987 Con_DPrintf("CL_ValidateState: no such frame %i in \"%s\" (which has %i frames)\n", s->frame, model->name, model->numframes);
1988 if (model && model->type && s->skin > 0 && s->skin >= model->numskins && !(s->lightpflags & PFLAGS_FULLDYNAMIC))
1989 Con_DPrintf("CL_ValidateState: no such skin %i in \"%s\" (which has %i skins)\n", s->skin, model->name, model->numskins);
1990 }
1991}

1993void CL_MoveLerpEntityStates(entity_t *ent)
1994{
1995 float odelta[3], adelta[3];
1996 VectorSubtract(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin, odelta);
1997 VectorSubtract(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles, adelta);
1998 if (!ent->state_previous.active || ent->state_previous.modelindex != ent->state_current.modelindex)
1999 {
2000 // reset all persistent stuff if this is a new entity
2001 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = 0;
2002 ent->persistent.lerpstarttime = cl.mtime[1];
2003 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.oldorigin);
2004 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.oldangles);
2005 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin);
2006 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles);
2007 // reset animation interpolation as well
2008 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].frame = ent->render.framegroupblend[1].frame = ent->state_current.frame;
2009 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].start = ent->render.framegroupblend[1].start = cl.time;
2010 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].lerp = 1;ent->render.framegroupblend[1].lerp = 0;
2011 ent->render.shadertime = cl.time;
2012 // reset various persistent stuff
2013 ent->persistent.muzzleflash = 0;
2014 ent->persistent.trail_allowed = false;
2015 }
2016 else if ((ent->state_previous.effects & EF_TELEPORT_BIT) != (ent->state_current.effects & EF_TELEPORT_BIT))
2017 {
2018 // don't interpolate the move
2019 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = 0;
2020 ent->persistent.lerpstarttime = cl.mtime[1];
2021 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.oldorigin);
2022 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.oldangles);
2023 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin);
2024 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles);
2025 ent->persistent.trail_allowed = false;
2026
2027 // if(ent->state_current.frame != ent->state_previous.frame)
2028 // do this even if we did change the frame
2029 // teleport bit is only used if an animation restart, or a jump, is necessary
2030 // so it should be always harmless to do this
2031 {
2032 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].frame = ent->render.framegroupblend[1].frame = ent->state_current.frame;
2033 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].start = ent->render.framegroupblend[1].start = cl.time;
2034 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].lerp = 1;ent->render.framegroupblend[1].lerp = 0;
2035 }
2036
2037 // note that this case must do everything the following case does too
2038 }
2039 else if ((ent->state_previous.effects & EF_RESTARTANIM_BIT) != (ent->state_current.effects & EF_RESTARTANIM_BIT))
2040 {
2041 ent->render.framegroupblend[1] = ent->render.framegroupblend[0];
2042 ent->render.framegroupblend[1].lerp = 1;
2043 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].frame = ent->state_current.frame;
2044 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].start = cl.time;
2045 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].lerp = 0;
2046 }
2047 else if (DotProduct(odelta, odelta) > 1000*1000
2048 || (cl.fixangle[0] && !cl.fixangle[1])
2049 || (ent->state_previous.tagindex != ent->state_current.tagindex)
2050 || (ent->state_previous.tagentity != ent->state_current.tagentity))
2051 {
2052 // don't interpolate the move
2053 // (the fixangle[] check detects teleports, but not constant fixangles
2054 // such as when spectating)
2055 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = 0;
2056 ent->persistent.lerpstarttime = cl.mtime[1];
2057 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.oldorigin);
2058 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.oldangles);
2059 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin);
2060 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles);
2061 ent->persistent.trail_allowed = false;
2062 }
2063 else if (ent->state_current.flags & RENDER_STEP)
2064 {
2065 // monster interpolation
2066 if (DotProduct(odelta, odelta) + DotProduct(adelta, adelta) > 0.01)
2067 {
2068 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = bound(0, cl.mtime[1] - ent->persistent.lerpstarttime, 0.1);
2069 ent->persistent.lerpstarttime = cl.mtime[1];
2070 VectorCopy(ent->persistent.neworigin, ent->persistent.oldorigin);
2071 VectorCopy(ent->persistent.newangles, ent->persistent.oldangles);
2072 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin);
2073 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles);
2074 }
2075 }
2076 else
2077 {
2078 // not a monster
2079 ent->persistent.lerpstarttime = ent->state_previous.time;
2080 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = bound(0, ent->state_current.time - ent->state_previous.time, 0.1);
2081 VectorCopy(ent->persistent.neworigin, ent->persistent.oldorigin);
2082 VectorCopy(ent->persistent.newangles, ent->persistent.oldangles);
2083 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.origin, ent->persistent.neworigin);
2084 VectorCopy(ent->state_current.angles, ent->persistent.newangles);
2085 }
2086 // trigger muzzleflash effect if necessary
2087 if (ent->state_current.effects & EF_MUZZLEFLASH)
2088 ent->persistent.muzzleflash = 1;
2089
2090 // restart animation bit
2091 if ((ent->state_previous.effects & EF_RESTARTANIM_BIT) != (ent->state_current.effects & EF_RESTARTANIM_BIT))
2092 {
2093 ent->render.framegroupblend[1] = ent->render.framegroupblend[0];
2094 ent->render.framegroupblend[1].lerp = 1;
2095 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].frame = ent->state_current.frame;
2096 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].start = cl.time;
2097 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].lerp = 0;
2098 }
2099}

2101/*
2102==================
2103CL_ParseBaseline
2104==================
2105*/
2106static void CL_ParseBaseline (entity_t *ent, int large)
2107{
2108 int i;
2109
2110 ent->state_baseline = defaultstate;
2111 // FIXME: set ent->state_baseline.number?
2112 ent->state_baseline.active = true;
2113 if (large)
2114 {
2115 ent->state_baseline.modelindex = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2116 ent->state_baseline.frame = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2117 }
2118 else if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
2119 {
2120 ent->state_baseline.modelindex = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2121 ent->state_baseline.frame = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2122 }
2123 else
2124 {
2125 ent->state_baseline.modelindex = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2126 ent->state_baseline.frame = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2127 }
2128 ent->state_baseline.colormap = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2129 ent->state_baseline.skin = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2130 for (i = 0;i < 3;i++)
2131 {
2132 ent->state_baseline.origin[i] = MSG_ReadCoord(&cl_message, cls.protocol);
2133 ent->state_baseline.angles[i] = MSG_ReadAngle(&cl_message, cls.protocol);
2134 }
2135 ent->state_previous = ent->state_current = ent->state_baseline;
2136}

2139/*
2140==================
2141CL_ParseClientdata
2142
2143Server information pertaining to this client only
2144==================
2145*/
2146static void CL_ParseClientdata (void)
2147{
2148 int i, bits;
2149
2150 VectorCopy (cl.mpunchangle[0], cl.mpunchangle[1]);
2151 VectorCopy (cl.mpunchvector[0], cl.mpunchvector[1]);
2152 VectorCopy (cl.mvelocity[0], cl.mvelocity[1]);
2153 cl.mviewzoom[1] = cl.mviewzoom[0];
2154
2155 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES5)
2156 {
2157 cl.stats[STAT_VIEWHEIGHT] = DEFAULT_VIEWHEIGHT;
2158 cl.stats[STAT_ITEMS] = 0;
2159 cl.stats[STAT_VIEWZOOM] = 255;
2160 }
2161 cl.idealpitch = 0;
2162 cl.mpunchangle[0][0] = 0;
2163 cl.mpunchangle[0][1] = 0;
2164 cl.mpunchangle[0][2] = 0;
2165 cl.mpunchvector[0][0] = 0;
2166 cl.mpunchvector[0][1] = 0;
2167 cl.mpunchvector[0][2] = 0;
2168 cl.mvelocity[0][0] = 0;
2169 cl.mvelocity[0][1] = 0;
2170 cl.mvelocity[0][2] = 0;
2171 cl.mviewzoom[0] = 1;
2172
2173 bits = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2174 if (bits & SU_EXTEND1)
2175 bits |= (MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) << 16);
2176 if (bits & SU_EXTEND2)
2177 bits |= (MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) << 24);
2178
2179 if (bits & SU_VIEWHEIGHT)
2180 cl.stats[STAT_VIEWHEIGHT] = MSG_ReadChar(&cl_message);
2181
2182 if (bits & SU_IDEALPITCH)
2183 cl.idealpitch = MSG_ReadChar(&cl_message);
2184
2185 for (i = 0;i < 3;i++)
2186 {
2187 if (bits & (SU_PUNCH1<<i) )
2188 {
2189 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
2190 cl.mpunchangle[0][i] = MSG_ReadChar(&cl_message);
2191 else
2192 cl.mpunchangle[0][i] = MSG_ReadAngle16i(&cl_message);
2193 }
2194 if (bits & (SU_PUNCHVEC1<<i))
2195 {
2196 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4)
2197 cl.mpunchvector[0][i] = MSG_ReadCoord16i(&cl_message);
2198 else
2199 cl.mpunchvector[0][i] = MSG_ReadCoord32f(&cl_message);
2200 }
2201 if (bits & (SU_VELOCITY1<<i) )
2202 {
2203 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4)
2204 cl.mvelocity[0][i] = MSG_ReadChar(&cl_message)*16;
2205 else
2206 cl.mvelocity[0][i] = MSG_ReadCoord32f(&cl_message);
2207 }
2208 }
2209
2210 // LadyHavoc: hipnotic demos don't have this bit set but should
2211 if (bits & SU_ITEMS || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES5)
2212 cl.stats[STAT_ITEMS] = MSG_ReadLong(&cl_message);
2213
2214 cl.onground = (bits & SU_ONGROUND) != 0;
2215 cl.inwater = (bits & SU_INWATER) != 0;
2216
2217 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES5)
2218 {
2219 cl.stats[STAT_WEAPONFRAME] = (bits & SU_WEAPONFRAME) ? MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message) : 0;
2220 cl.stats[STAT_ARMOR] = (bits & SU_ARMOR) ? MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message) : 0;
2221 cl.stats[STAT_WEAPON] = (bits & SU_WEAPON) ? MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message) : 0;
2222 cl.stats[STAT_HEALTH] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2223 cl.stats[STAT_AMMO] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2224 cl.stats[STAT_SHELLS] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2225 cl.stats[STAT_NAILS] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2226 cl.stats[STAT_ROCKETS] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2227 cl.stats[STAT_CELLS] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2228 cl.stats[STAT_ACTIVEWEAPON] = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2229 }
2230 else if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_QUAKEDP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRAMOVIE || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES1 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4)
2231 {
2232 cl.stats[STAT_WEAPONFRAME] = (bits & SU_WEAPONFRAME) ? MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) : 0;
2233 cl.stats[STAT_ARMOR] = (bits & SU_ARMOR) ? MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) : 0;
2234 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_NEHAHRABJP3)
2235 cl.stats[STAT_WEAPON] = (bits & SU_WEAPON) ? (unsigned short)MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message) : 0;
2236 else
2237 cl.stats[STAT_WEAPON] = (bits & SU_WEAPON) ? MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message) : 0;
2238 cl.stats[STAT_HEALTH] = MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2239 cl.stats[STAT_AMMO] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2240 cl.stats[STAT_SHELLS] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2241 cl.stats[STAT_NAILS] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2242 cl.stats[STAT_ROCKETS] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2243 cl.stats[STAT_CELLS] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2244 if (gamemode == GAME_HIPNOTIC || gamemode == GAME_ROGUE || gamemode == GAME_QUOTH || IS_OLDNEXUIZ_DERIVED(gamemode))
2245 cl.stats[STAT_ACTIVEWEAPON] = (1<<MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message));
2246 else
2247 cl.stats[STAT_ACTIVEWEAPON] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2248 }
2249
2250 if (bits & SU_VIEWZOOM)
2251 {
2252 if (cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES2 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES3 || cls.protocol == PROTOCOL_DARKPLACES4)
2253 cl.stats[STAT_VIEWZOOM] = MSG_ReadByte(&cl_message);
2254 else
2255 cl.stats[STAT_VIEWZOOM] = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2256 }
2257
2258 // viewzoom interpolation
2259 cl.mviewzoom[0] = (float) max(cl.stats[STAT_VIEWZOOM], 2) * (1.0f / 255.0f);
2260}

2263=====================
2264CL_ParseStatic
2265=====================
2266*/
2267static void CL_ParseStatic (int large)
2268{
2269 entity_t *ent;
2270
2271 if (cl.num_static_entities >= cl.max_static_entities)
2272 Host_Error ("Too many static entities");
2273 ent = &cl.static_entities[cl.num_static_entities++];
2274 CL_ParseBaseline (ent, large);
2275
2276 if (ent->state_baseline.modelindex == 0)
2277 {
2278 Con_DPrintf("svc_parsestatic: static entity without model at %f %f %f\n", ent->state_baseline.origin[0], ent->state_baseline.origin[1], ent->state_baseline.origin[2]);
2279 cl.num_static_entities--;
2280 // This is definitely a cheesy way to conserve resources...
2281 return;
2282 }
2283
2284// copy it to the current state
2285 ent->render.model = CL_GetModelByIndex(ent->state_baseline.modelindex);
2286 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].frame = ent->state_baseline.frame;
2287 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].lerp = 1;
2288 // make torchs play out of sync
2289 ent->render.framegroupblend[0].start = lhrandom(-10, -1);
2290 ent->render.skinnum = ent->state_baseline.skin;
2291 ent->render.effects = ent->state_baseline.effects;
2292 ent->render.alpha = 1;
2293
2294 //VectorCopy (ent->state_baseline.origin, ent->render.origin);
2295 //VectorCopy (ent->state_baseline.angles, ent->render.angles);
2296
2297 Matrix4x4_CreateFromQuakeEntity(&ent->render.matrix, ent->state_baseline.origin[0], ent->state_baseline.origin[1], ent->state_baseline.origin[2], ent->state_baseline.angles[0], ent->state_baseline.angles[1], ent->state_baseline.angles[2], 1);
2298 ent->render.allowdecals = true;
2299 CL_UpdateRenderEntity(&ent->render);
2300}

2358void CL_NewBeam (int ent, vec3_t start, vec3_t end, model_t *m, int lightning)
2359{
2360 int i;
2361 beam_t *b = NULL;
2362
2363 if (ent >= MAX_EDICTS)
2364 {
2365 Con_Printf("CL_NewBeam: invalid entity number %i\n", ent);
2366 ent = 0;
2367 }
2368
2369 if (ent >= cl.max_entities)
2370 CL_ExpandEntities(ent);
2371
2372 // override any beam with the same entity
2373 i = cl.max_beams;
2374 if (ent)
2375 for (i = 0, b = cl.beams;i < cl.max_beams;i++, b++)
2376 if (b->entity == ent)
2377 break;
2378 // if the entity was not found then just replace an unused beam
2379 if (i == cl.max_beams)
2380 for (i = 0, b = cl.beams;i < cl.max_beams;i++, b++)
2381 if (!b->model)
2382 break;
2383 if (i < cl.max_beams)
2384 {
2385 cl.num_beams = max(cl.num_beams, i + 1);
2386 b->entity = ent;
2387 b->lightning = lightning;
2388 b->model = m;
2389 b->endtime = cl.mtime[0] + 0.2;
2390 VectorCopy (start, b->start);
2391 VectorCopy (end, b->end);
2392 }
2393 else
2394 Con_DPrint("beam list overflow!\n");
2395}
2396
2397static void CL_ParseBeam (model_t *m, int lightning)
2398{
2399 int ent;
2400 vec3_t start, end;
2401
2402 ent = (unsigned short) MSG_ReadShort(&cl_message);
2403 MSG_ReadVector(&cl_message, start, cls.protocol);
2404 MSG_ReadVector(&cl_message, end, cls.protocol);
2405
2406 if (ent >= MAX_EDICTS)
2407 {
2408 Con_Printf("CL_ParseBeam: invalid entity number %i\n", ent);
2409 ent = 0;
2410 }
2411
2412 CL_NewBeam(ent, start, end, m, lightning);
2413}

2983typedef struct cl_iplog_item_s
2984{
2985 char *address;
2986 char *name;
2987}
2988cl_iplog_item_t;
2989
2990static qbool cl_iplog_loaded = false;
2991static int cl_iplog_numitems = 0;
2992static int cl_iplog_maxitems = 0;
2993static cl_iplog_item_t *cl_iplog_items;
2994
2995static void CL_IPLog_Load(void);
2996static void CL_IPLog_Add(const char *address, const char *name, qbool checkexisting, qbool addtofile)
2997{
2998 int i;
2999 size_t sz_name, sz_address;
3000 if (!address || !address[0] || !name || !name[0])
3001 return;
3002 if (!cl_iplog_loaded)
3003 CL_IPLog_Load();
3004 if (developer_extra.integer)
3005 Con_DPrintf("CL_IPLog_Add(\"%s\", \"%s\", %i, %i);\n", address, name, checkexisting, addtofile);
3006 // see if it already exists
3007 if (checkexisting)
3008 {
3009 for (i = 0;i < cl_iplog_numitems;i++)
3010 {
3011 if (!strcmp(cl_iplog_items[i].address, address) && !strcmp(cl_iplog_items[i].name, name))
3012 {
3013 if (developer_extra.integer)
3014 Con_DPrintf("... found existing \"%s\" \"%s\"\n", cl_iplog_items[i].address, cl_iplog_items[i].name);
3015 return;
3016 }
3017 }
3018 }
3019 // it does not already exist in the iplog, so add it
3020 if (cl_iplog_maxitems <= cl_iplog_numitems || !cl_iplog_items)
3021 {
3022 cl_iplog_item_t *olditems = cl_iplog_items;
3023 cl_iplog_maxitems = max(1024, cl_iplog_maxitems + 256);
3024 cl_iplog_items = (cl_iplog_item_t *) Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, cl_iplog_maxitems * sizeof(cl_iplog_item_t));
3025 if (olditems)
3026 {
3027 if (cl_iplog_numitems)
3028 memcpy(cl_iplog_items, olditems, cl_iplog_numitems * sizeof(cl_iplog_item_t));
3029 Mem_Free(olditems);
3030 }
3031 }
3032 sz_address = strlen(address) + 1;
3033 sz_name = strlen(name) + 1;
3034 cl_iplog_items[cl_iplog_numitems].address = (char *) Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, sz_address);
3035 cl_iplog_items[cl_iplog_numitems].name = (char *) Mem_Alloc(cls.permanentmempool, sz_name);
3036 dp_strlcpy(cl_iplog_items[cl_iplog_numitems].address, address, sz_address);
3037 // TODO: maybe it would be better to strip weird characters from name when
3038 // copying it here rather than using a straight strcpy?
3039 dp_strlcpy(cl_iplog_items[cl_iplog_numitems].name, name, sz_name);
3040 cl_iplog_numitems++;
3041 if (addtofile)
3042 {
3043 // add it to the iplog.txt file
3044 // TODO: this ought to open the one in the userpath version of the base
3045 // gamedir, not the current gamedir
3046// not necessary for mobile
3047#ifndef DP_MOBILETOUCH
3048 Log_Printf(cl_iplog_name.string, "%s %s\n", address, name);
3049 if (developer_extra.integer)
3050 Con_DPrintf("CL_IPLog_Add: appending this line to %s: %s %s\n", cl_iplog_name.string, address, name);
3051#endif
3052 }
3053}
3054
3055static void CL_IPLog_Load(void)
3056{
3057 int i, len, linenumber;
3058 char *text, *textend;
3059 unsigned char *filedata;
3060 fs_offset_t filesize;
3061 char line[MAX_INPUTLINE];
3062 char address[MAX_INPUTLINE];
3063 cl_iplog_loaded = true;
3064 // TODO: this ought to open the one in the userpath version of the base
3065 // gamedir, not the current gamedir
3066// not necessary for mobile
3067#ifndef DP_MOBILETOUCH
3068 filedata = FS_LoadFile(cl_iplog_name.string, tempmempool, true, &filesize);
3069#else
3070 filedata = NULL;
3071#endif
3072 if (!filedata)
3073 return;
3074 text = (char *)filedata;
3075 textend = text + filesize;
3076 for (linenumber = 1;text < textend;linenumber++)
3077 {
3078 for (len = 0;text < textend && *text != '\r' && *text != '\n';text++)
3079 if (len < (int)sizeof(line) - 1)
3080 line[len++] = *text;
3081 line[len] = 0;
3082 if (text < textend && *text == '\r' && text[1] == '\n')
3083 text++;
3084 if (text < textend && *text == '\n')
3085 text++;
3086 if (line[0] == '/' && line[1] == '/')
3087 continue; // skip comments if anyone happens to add them
3088 for (i = 0;i < len && !ISWHITESPACE(line[i]);i++)
3089 address[i] = line[i];
3090 address[i] = 0;
3091 // skip exactly one space character
3092 i++;
3093 // address contains the address with termination,
3094 // line + i contains the name with termination
3095 if (address[0] && line[i])
3096 CL_IPLog_Add(address, line + i, false, false);
3097 else
3098 Con_Printf("%s:%i: could not parse address and name:\n%s\n", cl_iplog_name.string, linenumber, line);
3099 }
3100}

3102static void CL_IPLog_List_f(cmd_state_t *cmd)
3103{
3104 int i, j;
3105 const char *addressprefix;
3106 if (Cmd_Argc(cmd) > 2)
3107 {
3108 Con_Printf("usage: %s 123.456.789.\n", Cmd_Argv(cmd, 0));
3109 return;
3110 }
3111 addressprefix = "";
3112 if (Cmd_Argc(cmd) >= 2)
3113 addressprefix = Cmd_Argv(cmd, 1);
3114 if (!cl_iplog_loaded)
3115 CL_IPLog_Load();
3116 if (addressprefix && addressprefix[0])
3117 Con_Printf("Listing iplog addresses beginning with %s\n", addressprefix);
3118 else
3119 Con_Printf("Listing all iplog entries\n");
3120 Con_Printf("address name\n");
3121 for (i = 0;i < cl_iplog_numitems;i++)
3122 {
3123 if (addressprefix && addressprefix[0])
3124 {
3125 for (j = 0;addressprefix[j];j++)
3126 if (addressprefix[j] != cl_iplog_items[i].address[j])
3127 break;
3128 // if this address does not begin with the addressprefix string
3129 // simply omit it from the output
3130 if (addressprefix[j])
3131 continue;
3132 }
3133 // if name is less than 15 characters, left justify it and pad
3134 // if name is more than 15 characters, print all of it, not worrying
3135 // about the fact it will misalign the columns
3136 if (strlen(cl_iplog_items[i].address) < 15)
3137 Con_Printf("%-15s %s\n", cl_iplog_items[i].address, cl_iplog_items[i].name);
3138 else
3139 Con_Printf("%5s %s\n", cl_iplog_items[i].address, cl_iplog_items[i].name);
3140 }

3143// look for anything interesting like player IP addresses or ping reports
3144static qbool CL_ExaminePrintString(const char *text)
3145{
3146 int len;
3147 const char *t;
3148 char temp[MAX_INPUTLINE];
3149 if (!strcmp(text, "Client ping times:\n"))
3150 {
3151 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_PING;
3152 // hide ping reports in demos
3153 if (cls.demoplayback)
3154 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = 1;
3155 for(cl.parsingtextplayerindex = 0; cl.parsingtextplayerindex < cl.maxclients && !cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name[0]; cl.parsingtextplayerindex++)
3156 ;
3157 if (cl.parsingtextplayerindex >= cl.maxclients) // should never happen, since the client itself should be in cl.scores
3158 {
3159 Con_Printf("ping reply but empty scoreboard?!?\n");
3160 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_NONE;
3161 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = 0;
3162 }
3163 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores ? 2 : 0;
3164 return !cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores;
3165 }
3166 if (!strncmp(text, "host: ", 9))
3167 {
3168 // cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = false; // really?
3169 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS;
3170 cl.parsingtextplayerindex = 0;
3171 return true;
3172 }
3173 if (cl.parsingtextmode == CL_PARSETEXTMODE_PING)
3174 {
3175 // if anything goes wrong, we'll assume this is not a ping report
3176 qbool expected = cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores != 0;
3177 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = 0;
3178 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_NONE;
3179 t = text;
3180 while (*t == ' ')
3181 t++;
3182 if ((*t >= '0' && *t <= '9') || *t == '-')
3183 {
3184 int ping = atoi(t);
3185 while ((*t >= '0' && *t <= '9') || *t == '-')
3186 t++;
3187 if (*t == ' ')
3188 {
3189 int charindex = 0;
3190 t++;
3191 if(cl.parsingtextplayerindex < cl.maxclients)
3192 {
3193 for (charindex = 0;cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name[charindex] == t[charindex];charindex++)
3194 ;
3195 // note: the matching algorithm stops at the end of the player name because some servers append text such as " READY" after the player name in the scoreboard but not in the ping report
3196 //if (cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name[charindex] == 0 && t[charindex] == '\n')
3197 if (t[charindex] == '\n')
3198 {
3199 cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].qw_ping = bound(0, ping, 9999);
3200 for (cl.parsingtextplayerindex++;cl.parsingtextplayerindex < cl.maxclients && !cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name[0];cl.parsingtextplayerindex++)
3201 ;
3202 //if (cl.parsingtextplayerindex < cl.maxclients) // we could still get unconnecteds!
3203 {
3204 // we parsed a valid ping entry, so expect another to follow
3205 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_PING;
3206 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = expected;
3207 }
3208 return !expected;
3209 }
3210 }
3211 if (!strncmp(t, "unconnected\n", 12))
3212 {
3213 // just ignore
3214 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_PING;
3215 cl.parsingtextexpectingpingforscores = expected;
3216 return !expected;
3217 }
3218 else
3219 Con_DPrintf("player names '%s' and '%s' didn't match\n", cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name, t);
3220 }
3221 }
3222 }
3223 if (cl.parsingtextmode == CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS)
3224 {
3225 if (!strncmp(text, "players: ", 9))
3226 {
3227 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS_PLAYERID;
3228 cl.parsingtextplayerindex = 0;
3229 return true;
3230 }
3231 else if (!strstr(text, ": "))
3232 {
3233 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_NONE; // status report ended
3234 return true;
3235 }
3236 }
3237 if (cl.parsingtextmode == CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS_PLAYERID)
3238 {
3239 // if anything goes wrong, we'll assume this is not a status report
3240 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_NONE;
3241 if (text[0] == '#' && text[1] >= '0' && text[1] <= '9')
3242 {
3243 t = text + 1;
3244 cl.parsingtextplayerindex = atoi(t) - 1;
3245 while (*t >= '0' && *t <= '9')
3246 t++;
3247 if (*t == ' ')
3248 {
3249 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS_PLAYERIP;
3250 return true;
3251 }
3252 // the player name follows here, along with frags and time
3253 }
3254 }
3255 if (cl.parsingtextmode == CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS_PLAYERIP)
3256 {
3257 // if anything goes wrong, we'll assume this is not a status report
3258 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_NONE;
3259 if (text[0] == ' ')
3260 {
3261 t = text;
3262 while (*t == ' ')
3263 t++;
3264 for (len = 0;*t && *t != '\n';t++)
3265 if (len < (int)sizeof(temp) - 1)
3266 temp[len++] = *t;
3267 temp[len] = 0;
3268 // botclient is perfectly valid, but we don't care about bots
3269 // also don't try to look up the name of an invalid player index
3270 if (strcmp(temp, "botclient")
3271 && cl.parsingtextplayerindex >= 0
3272 && cl.parsingtextplayerindex < cl.maxclients
3273 && cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name[0])
3274 {
3275 // log the player name and IP address string
3276 // (this operates entirely on strings to avoid issues with the
3277 // nature of a network address)
3278 CL_IPLog_Add(temp, cl.scores[cl.parsingtextplayerindex].name, true, true);
3279 }
3280 cl.parsingtextmode = CL_PARSETEXTMODE_STATUS_PLAYERID;
3281 return true;
3282 }
3283 }
3284 return true;
3285}
