3287extern cvar_t host_timescale;
3288extern cvar_t cl_lerpexcess;
3289static void CL_NetworkTimeReceived(double newtime)
3290{
3291 cl.opt_inputs_since_update = 0;
3292 cl.mtime[1] = cl.mtime[0];
3293 cl.mtime[0] = newtime;
3294 if (cls.timedemo || cl.mtime[1] == cl.mtime[0] || cls.signon < SIGNONS)
3295 cl.time = cl.mtime[1] = newtime;
3296 else if (cls.demoplayback)
3297 {
3298 // when time falls behind during demo playback it means the cl.mtime[1] was altered
3299 // due to a large time gap, so treat it as an instant change in time
3300 // (this can also happen during heavy packet loss in the demo)
3301 if (cl.time < newtime - 0.1)
3302 cl.mtime[1] = cl.time = newtime;
3303 }
3304 else if (cls.protocol != PROTOCOL_QUAKEWORLD)
3305 {
3306 double timehigh = 0; // hush compiler warning
3307 cl.mtime[1] = max(cl.mtime[1], cl.mtime[0] - 0.1);
3308
3309 if (developer_extra.integer && vid_activewindow)
3310 {
3311 if (cl.time < cl.mtime[1] - (cl.mtime[0] - cl.mtime[1]))
3312 Con_DPrintf("--- cl.time < cl.mtime[1] (%f < %f ... %f)\n", cl.time, cl.mtime[1], cl.mtime[0]);
3313 else if (cl.time > cl.mtime[0] + (cl.mtime[0] - cl.mtime[1]))
3314 Con_DPrintf("--- cl.time > cl.mtime[0] (%f > %f ... %f)\n", cl.time, cl.mtime[1], cl.mtime[0]);
3315 }
3316
3317selectmode:
3318 switch (cl_nettimesyncboundmode.integer)
3319 {
3320 default:
3321 Cvar_SetQuick(&cl_nettimesyncboundmode, cl_nettimesyncboundmode.defstring);
3322 goto selectmode;
3323 case 1:
3324 case 2:
3325 case 3:
3326 // doesn't make sense for modes > 3
3327 cl.time += (cl.mtime[1] - cl.time) * bound(0, cl_nettimesyncfactor.value, 1);
3328 timehigh = cl.mtime[1] + (cl.mtime[0] - cl.mtime[1]) * cl_nettimesyncboundtolerance.value;
3329 switch (cl_nettimesyncboundmode.integer)
3330 {
3331 case 1:
3332 cl.time = bound(cl.mtime[1], cl.time, cl.mtime[0]);
3333 break;
3334 case 2:
3335 if (cl.time < cl.mtime[1] || cl.time > timehigh)
3336 cl.time = cl.mtime[1];
3337 break;
3338 case 3:
3339 if ((cl.time < cl.mtime[1] && cl.oldtime < cl.mtime[1]) || (cl.time > timehigh && cl.oldtime > timehigh))
3340 cl.time = cl.mtime[1];
3341 break;
3342 }
3343 break;
3344
3345 case 4:
3346 if (fabs(cl.time - cl.mtime[1]) > 0.5)
3347 cl.time = cl.mtime[1]; // reset
3348 else if (fabs(cl.time - cl.mtime[1]) > 0.1)
3349 cl.time += 0.5 * (cl.mtime[1] - cl.time); // fast
3350 else if (cl.time > cl.mtime[1])
3351 cl.time -= 0.002 * cl.movevars_timescale; // fall into the past by 2ms
3352 else
3353 cl.time += 0.001 * cl.movevars_timescale; // creep forward 1ms
3354 break;
3355
3356 case 5:
3357 if (fabs(cl.time - cl.mtime[1]) > 0.5)
3358 cl.time = cl.mtime[1]; // reset
3359 else if (fabs(cl.time - cl.mtime[1]) > 0.1)
3360 cl.time += 0.5 * (cl.mtime[1] - cl.time); // fast
3361 else
3362 cl.time = bound(cl.time - 0.002 * cl.movevars_timescale, cl.mtime[1], cl.time + 0.001 * cl.movevars_timescale);
3363 break;
3364
3365 case 6:
3366 cl.time = bound(cl.mtime[1], cl.time, cl.mtime[0]);
3367 cl.time = bound(cl.time - 0.002 * cl.movevars_timescale, cl.mtime[1], cl.time + 0.001 * cl.movevars_timescale);
3368 break;
3369
3370 case 7:
3371 /* bones_was_here: this aims to prevent disturbances in the force from affecting cl.time
3372 * the rolling harmonic mean gives large time error outliers low significance
3373 * correction rate is dynamic and gradual (max 10% of mean error per tic)
3374 * time is correct within a few server frames of connect/map start
3375 * can achieve microsecond accuracy when cl.realframetime is a multiple of sv.frametime
3376 * prevents 0ms move frame times with uncapped fps
3377 * smoothest mode esp. for vsynced clients on servers with aggressive inputtimeout
3378 */
3379 {
3380 unsigned char i;
3381 float error;
3382 // in event of packet loss, cl.mtime[1] could be very old, so avoid if possible
3383 double target = cl.movevars_ticrate ? cl.mtime[0] - cl.movevars_ticrate : cl.mtime[1];
3384 cl.ts_error_stor[cl.ts_error_num] = 1.0f / max(fabs(cl.time - target), FLT_MIN);
3385 cl.ts_error_num = (cl.ts_error_num + 1) % NUM_TS_ERRORS;
3386 for (i = 0, error = 0.0f; i < NUM_TS_ERRORS; i++)
3387 error += cl.ts_error_stor[i];
3388 error = 0.1f / (error / NUM_TS_ERRORS);
3389 cl.time = bound(cl.time - error, target, cl.time + error);
3390 }
3391 break;
3392 }
3393 }
3394 // this packet probably contains a player entity update, so we will need
3395 // to update the prediction
3396 cl.movement_replay = true;
3397 // this may get updated later in parsing by svc_clientdata
3398 cl.onground = false;
3399 // if true the cl.viewangles are interpolated from cl.mviewangles[]
3400 // during this frame
3401 // (makes spectating players much smoother and prevents mouse movement from turning)
3402 cl.fixangle[1] = cl.fixangle[0];
3403 cl.fixangle[0] = false;
3404 if (!cls.demoplayback)
3405 VectorCopy(cl.mviewangles[0], cl.mviewangles[1]);
3406 // update the csqc's server timestamps, critical for proper sync
3407 CSQC_UpdateNetworkTimes(cl.mtime[0], cl.mtime[1]);
3408
3409#ifdef USEODE
3410 if (cl.mtime[0] > cl.mtime[1])
3411 World_Physics_Frame(&cl.world, cl.mtime[0] - cl.mtime[1], cl.movevars_gravity);
3412#endif
3413
3414 // only lerp entities that also get an update in this frame, when lerp excess is used
3415 if(cl_lerpexcess.value > 0)
3416 {
3417 int i;
3418 for (i = 1;i < cl.num_entities;i++)
3419 {
3420 if (cl.entities_active[i])
3421 {
3422 entity_t *ent = cl.entities + i;
3423 ent->persistent.lerpdeltatime = 0;
3424 }
3425 }
3426 }
3427}
